# EKS Module

This Terraform module creates Amazon Elastic Kubernetes Service (EKS) clusters, managed node groups, and related resources for both development and production environments.

## Features

- ✅ **EKS Cluster** - Create EKS with configurable endpoint access and logging
- ✅ **Managed Node Groups** - Create default and additional node groups
- ✅ **IAM Roles** - Create cluster and node IAM roles with policy attachments
- ✅ **IRSA Support** - Optional OIDC provider for IAM Roles for Service Accounts
- ✅ **EKS Add-ons** - Manage core add-ons like CoreDNS, VPC CNI, and kube-proxy
- ✅ **CloudWatch Logs** - Configure control-plane log retention
- ✅ **Security Group** - Optional dedicated cluster security group
- ✅ **Deletion Protection** - Toggle EKS deletion protection with safe lag
- ✅ **Tagging** - Unified tagging across cluster resources
- ✅ **Cost Controls** - Support SPOT capacity in additional node groups

## Usage

### Call from another repository

Point `source` at this repo and the path under it (`//Aws/EKS`). Pin **`ref` to a tag or commit** in production, not a branch that can change.

```hcl
module "eks" {
  source = "git::https://github.com/saurabhrsahu/terraform-modules.git//Aws/EKS?ref=main"
  # Use ?ref=v1.0.0 (or a commit SHA) once you tag releases
  # ...same inputs as in Basic Usage below
}
```

The **root** module where you call this must configure the **AWS** provider and authentication. This module only declares it needs `hashicorp/aws` and `hashicorp/time`.

```hcl
terraform {
  required_providers {
    aws = {
      source  = "hashicorp/aws"
      version = ">= 5.0.0, < 6.0.0"
    }
    time = {
      source  = "hashicorp/time"
      version = ">= 0.9.0"
    }
  }
}

provider "aws" {
  region = var.region
}
```

`provider "time"` is optional; the default `time` provider is enough for this module.

### Basic Usage

```hcl
module "eks" {
  source = "../../modules/Aws/EKS"

  cluster_name = "my-eks"
  region       = "us-east-1"
  vpc_id       = "vpc-0123456789abcdef0"
  subnet_ids   = [
    "subnet-0123456789abcdef0",
    "subnet-0123456789abcdef1"
  ]

  default_node_group = {
    name           = "system"
    instance_types = ["t3.medium"]
    desired_size   = 2
    min_size       = 1
    max_size       = 3
  }

  additional_node_groups = {
    app = {
      name           = "app"
      instance_types = ["t3.large"]
      capacity_type  = "SPOT"
      desired_size   = 1
      min_size       = 0
      max_size       = 2
    }
  }

  common_tags = {
    Environment = "dev"
    Team        = "platform"
  }
}
```

## Inputs

| Name | Description | Type | Default | Required |
|------|-------------|------|---------|:--------:|
| `cluster_name` | EKS cluster name | `string` | n/a | yes |
| `region` | AWS region | `string` | `"us-east-1"` | no |
| `vpc_id` | VPC for EKS | `string` | n/a | yes |
| `subnet_ids` | Subnets for control plane and nodes | `list(string)` | n/a | yes |
| `default_node_group` | Primary managed node group config | `object` | n/a | yes |
| `additional_node_groups` | Map of additional node groups | `map(object)` | `{}` | no |
| `endpoint_public_access` | Enable public API endpoint | `bool` | `true` | no |
| `endpoint_private_access` | Enable private API endpoint | `bool` | `true` | no |
| `public_access_cidrs` | Allowed CIDRs for public endpoint | `list(string)` | `["0.0.0.0/0"]` | no |
| `cluster_addons` | EKS add-ons to install | `map(object)` | core add-ons | no |
| `enable_irsa` | Create OIDC provider for IRSA | `bool` | `true` | no |
| `deletion_protection` | Enable cluster deletion protection | `bool` | `false` | no |

## Outputs

| Name | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `cluster` | Core attributes of the EKS cluster |
| `cluster_name` | Name of the EKS cluster |
| `cluster_arn` | ARN of the EKS cluster |
| `cluster_endpoint` | API server endpoint |
| `cluster_certificate_authority_data` | Cluster CA data (sensitive) |
| `node_groups` | Default and additional node groups |
| `addons` | Installed EKS add-ons |
| `iam` | IAM roles and OIDC provider details |
| `connection_info` | AWS CLI command for kubeconfig |
| `security_info` | Endpoint, KMS, IRSA, and deletion settings |

## Requirements

| Name | Version |
|------|---------|
| terraform | >= 1.3.0 |
| aws | >= 5.0.0, < 6.0.0 |
| time | >= 0.9.0 |

## Providers

| Name | Version |
|------|---------|
| aws | >= 5.0.0, < 6.0.0 |
| time | >= 0.9.0 |
